Description: 
Augustus Northmore Welby Pugin is far from being a 
household name, yet he designed the iconic clock
tower of Big Ben as well as much of the Palace of 
Westminster. The 19th century Gothic Revival that Pugin 
inspired, with its medieval influences and soaring church 
spires, established an image of Britain which still defines 
the nation. Presenter Richard Taylor charts Pugin's 
extraordinary life story and discovers how his work 
continues to influence Britain today
